T1  - The specification and power of tests to detect abnormal changes in corporate investment
AU  - Alderson, Michael J.
AU  - Betker, Brian L.
JO  - Journal of Corporate Finance
VL  - 12
IS  - 4
SP  - 738
EP  - 760
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/09/01/
SN  - 0929-1199
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jcorpfin.2005.07.001
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0929119905000581
KW  - Capital expenditures
KW  - Corporate investment
KW  - Event studies
AB  - We evaluate methods used to measure abnormal changes in capital expenditures. We examine both statistical tests and models of expected capital expenditures. We find that commonly used research designs yield test statistics that are misspecified, even in random samples. In cases where sample firms share a common characteristic such as extremely low or high investment, size, leverage, return on assets or market-to-book ratio, it is very important to match sample firms to a control group that shares this pre-event characteristic. We also find that using control groups, rather than a single control firm, yields more powerful test statistics.
